        <p>The income approach focuses on the practice's ability to generate future cash flows:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Discounted Cash Flow (DCF):</strong> Projects future earnings and discounts them to present value</li>
          <li><strong>Capitalization of Earnings:</strong> Uses a capitalization rate applied to normalized earnings</li>
          <li><strong>SDE Multiple Method:</strong> Applies industry multiples to seller's discretionary earnings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Market Approach</h3>
        <p>Compares your practice to similar practices that have recently sold:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Analyzes comparable sales data</li>
          <li>Adjusts for differences in size, location, and specialty</li>
