        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What is the difference between practice value and practice price?</h3>
          <p>Practice value is the estimated worth based on financial analysis and market conditions, while practice price is the actual amount paid in a transaction. Price can vary from value based on negotiation, market timing, buyer motivation, and specific transaction terms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
